author: News Sentinel staff
title: px-roundup22 - PrepXtra
text:
Webb School's volleyball team lacked its typical polish on Wednesday, but still advanced to the semifinals in the TSSAA Division II-A state tournament at Murfreesboro Siegel High School.
The Lady Spartans, chasing their third consecutive state title, overcame 19 errors to get past Collierville St. George's 25-16, 19-25, 25-12, 25-12.
Webb (51-4) will take on Harding Academy in Thursday's 11 a.m. semifinal at Middle Tennessee State. The Lady Spartans beat the Lady Lions in two sets on Aug. 29.
"We kind of fell asleep in one set," Webb coach Chris Hames said by phone on Wednesday. "They're a big team. They blocked us well. Harding is probably a better matchup for us, more of a ball control team."
Class A
Concord Christian Rolls: Concord Christian won six of seven sets on Wednesday to advance to Thursday's semifinal.
Allie Koepfer totaled 21 kills and Sidney Sherrill added 19 as the Lady Lions rolled past Middleton 25-10, 25-17, 25-4 in their opening game at Blackman High School, before topping Jackson County 17-25, 25-18, 25-12, 25-23 to advance. The Lady Lions will take on South Greene at 2 p.m. on Thursday at MTSU.
The Lady Rebels upset Goodpasture Christian, which has won three consecutive championships, the past two in Class A, to advance.
